@startuml
title Cloud Continuity Architecture
left to right direction

' Palette
' #211951 (deep navy)
' #836FFF (violet)
' #15F5BA (mint)
' #F0F3FF (soft white)

skinparam backgroundColor #F0F3FF
skinparam shadowing false
skinparam defaultFontName Segoe UI
skinparam defaultFontColor #211951

skinparam ArrowColor #211951
skinparam ArrowThickness 1
skinparam package {
  BorderColor #211951
  FontColor #211951
  BackgroundColor #F0F3FF
}

skinparam rectangle {
  BorderColor #211951
  FontColor #211951
  BackgroundColor #F0F3FF
}

skinparam rectangle<<primary>> {
  BackgroundColor #836FFF
  BorderColor #211951
  FontColor #F0F3FF
}

skinparam rectangle<<secondary>> {
  BackgroundColor #15F5BA
  BorderColor #211951
  FontColor #211951
}

skinparam rectangle<<external>> {
  BackgroundColor #211951
  BorderColor #211951
  FontColor #F0F3FF
}

skinparam rectangle<<neutral>> {
  BackgroundColor #F0F3FF
  BorderColor #211951
  FontColor #211951
}

rectangle "Customers" as U <<neutral>>
rectangle "DNS + Edge Protection" as DNS <<external>>

package "Primary Region" {
  rectangle "Web Frontend" as PWEB <<primary>>
  rectangle "API Layer" as PAPI <<primary>>
  rectangle "Primary Database" as PDB <<primary>>
}

package "Secondary Region" {
  rectangle "Web Frontend" as SWEB <<secondary>>
  rectangle "API Layer" as SAPI <<secondary>>
  rectangle "Secondary DB Replica" as SDB <<secondary>>
}

package "Third-Party Dependencies" {
  rectangle "Identity Provider" as IDP <<external>>
  rectangle "Payment Processor" as PAY <<external>>
}

package "Operations" {
  rectangle "Monitoring + Alerting" as MON <<neutral>>
  rectangle "Incident Response Team" as IR <<neutral>>
  rectangle "Status Communication" as COMMS <<neutral>>
}

U --> DNS
DNS --> PWEB
DNS --> SWEB

PWEB --> PAPI
SWEB --> SAPI

PAPI --> PDB
SAPI --> SDB
PDB ..> SDB : replication

PAPI --> IDP
SAPI --> IDP
PAPI --> PAY
SAPI --> PAY

PAPI --> MON
SAPI --> MON
MON --> IR
IR --> COMMS

legend right
|= Type |= Color |
| Primary Region Services | #836FFF |
| Secondary Region Services | #15F5BA |
| External Dependencies | #211951 |
| Neutral Background / Ops | #F0F3FF |
endlegend

note bottom of COMMS
Plain-English guide:
1) Customers enter through DNS + Edge Protection (the front door).
2) Traffic normally goes to the Primary Region (violet boxes).
3) If the primary side has issues, traffic can go to the Secondary Region (mint boxes).
4) Both regions rely on outside providers for login and payments (dark navy boxes).
5) Database replication means key data is copied to the secondary side for recovery.
6) Monitoring alerts the incident team, and that team sends status updates.
In short: the diagram shows how the shop keeps working or recovers faster when one part fails.
end note

@enduml